Prague's public transport will ride on a chip for the first time on Wednesday
Wednesday, 1 October 2008 will go down in the history of the Prague Public Transport Company as the date when the first passengers will board the metro, trams and buses and will have an electronic coupon in their pocket instead of a paper ticket.
At the moment, about one hundred thousand people who own an Opencard chip card can buy it.
Passengers can purchase a 30-day, 90-day and annual coupon (which will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it uploaded to their chip card at the information centres and workplaces of the Transport Company at the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
Since yesterday, coupons can also be purchased over the Internet on the website of the www.dpp.cz Public Transit Company.
The service was used by over four hundred customers in the afternoon.
Those who start using the online store can definitely forget about the dispensing windows in metro stations, where they had to regularly stand in long queues for paper tickets.
They buy the coupon over the Internet and upload it to their Opencard at one of the thirteen branches of the Municipal Library.
"At these locations, passengers are provided with a counter with trained staff, which will help those interested with online shopping and also upload the purchased coupon to their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
In addition to libraries, it will also be possible to upload electronic coupons to Opencard in self-service vending machines that are installed in several metro vestibules.
What do such slots look like?
They are red, resemble ticket markers, and passengers may have already noticed them at the Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská metro stations.
"Now there are five of them in the city, but by the end of the year there should be eighty," Opatrný added.
The coupon will check the driver's place automatic
The operation of the vending machines that will start working tomorrow is simple.
Just insert the Opencard chip card into them and the previously paid coupon will load itself onto it.
Electronic coupons from tomorrow are valid not only in the capital, but also in its surroundings.
