Questions after the accident: Are stewards on the bus illegal?
The law does not know them, walking in a long-distance bus is not allowed
The tragic accident involving a Student Agency bus near Padua, Italy, has raised the question of whether stewards and passengers can move around the bus while driving.
"If we want to strictly and formally comply with the law, the steward's activity is contrary to the Road Traffic Act," says Karel Hanzelka, spokesman for the Ministry of Transport.
The accident that killed a twenty-two-year-old stewardess last week was apparently caused by a truck driver who crossed the path of the bus.
Unfortunately, the girl was sitting next to the driver, in the least safe place in the car, although she has two other seats reserved.
However, the bus can crash or brake sharply, even when the steward is delivering coffee or newspapers.
The role is played by whether the bus is equipped with standing places according to the technical certificate.
If the bus is not homologated, passengers must be seated.
Student Agency coaches do not have standing spaces; which was Aktuálně.cz confirmed by the director of the company, Radim Jančura.
"We discussed this with the ministry and at first it did not allow the movement of passengers.
Later they called it off and we came to the conclusion that passengers are allowed to go to the toilet while driving, as long as they have their seat," he said.
The law does not know the steward
"There is no clear legal interpretation of the steward's role – no legislation addresses that role.
However, no legal regulation prohibits the carrier from providing services.
The Road Transport Act only knows the term conductor of vehicles; it does not define its rights and obligations," adds Hanzelka's spokesperson less clearly.
On the other hand, Josef Pokorný, Director of the Department of Road Vehicles Operation of the Ministry of Transport, believes that the law adequately addresses the issue.
"It depends on whether the bus is allowed standing in the homologation.
