Buses are divided into urban buses, with standing places and maximum speed limits, interurban buses with standing places with a higher speed limit, and long-distance buses without standing places with a speed limit and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like an airplane, says expert
BESIP traffic safety expert Jaroslav Hořín does not see a major problem in the movement of stewards on board the bus.
"There are not many dangers during smooth driving, the situation can be compared to servicing in airplanes.
Even here, it's uncertain when the turbulence will come and the flight attendant may hit her head."
"However, if the bus brakes sharply, of course the laws of physics apply.
Just like in a city bus or tram.
The safety of stewards must be dealt with by the carrier by internal regulations," he says, and also thinks that from the point of view of the law, the issue is unresolved.
Jancura is willing to cancel the services
Student Agency offers steward services as the only bus company.
