Bail for Bangladeshi ex-PM denied
A Bangladeshi court has rejected former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina Wajid's request for bail, meaning she could be arrested if she returns to her homeland.
Her lawyers said the court refused to grant her bail in connection with allegations that she had blackmailed over fifty million taka ($729,700) from a businessman when she was prime minister.
