A week after revealing their preliminary agreement, the two banks explained that MUFG intends to buy 9.9% of Morgan Stanley's common stock at a single price of $25.25, totaling $3 billion.
The agreed price is 19% lower than the book value of the securities as of August 31.
MUFG is investing another six billion dollars to acquire convertible securities that provide a 10% yield and have an exchange price of $31.25.
