Morgan Stanley's new statute was adopted last week, allowing it to diversify its activities, but placing it under the supervision of the Federal Reserve Bank.
Its merger with MUFG also confirms that the current financial crisis is forcing Wall Street's biggest aces to take a much more cautious approach than before.
