Járóková: The vicious circle of poverty and segregation must be broken
The European Equality Summit, hosted this year by France, the current presiding country of the European Union, began today in Paris.
In her message to the plenary, Lívia Járóka, a Fidesz MEP for the European People's Party, drew attention to segregation in education, as one of the main speakers of expert deliberations addressed to the plenary, as it is one of the most serious injustices affecting Roma children and, moreover, the most serious obstacle to their application.
