Open Office, we have here the third edition of the package"anti-Microsoft»
It is the day of the release of Open Office.org 3.0, an open source personal production package that aims to penetrate more and more users, from home to office, from experts to public administration, as a free alternative to the better-known Microsoft Office.
After about a year of work by volunteers controlled by the SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office is presented to the general public with various innovations: the welcome screen and the revised and improved opening window will be joined by other, much more important, such as compatibility for Apple's Mac OS X operating system and support for the new Open Document Format (ODF) 1.2, the latest standard ISO version.
Emphasis is also placed on cooperation with the Office 2007 package, Open Office is able to open a document with a new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx).
Interesting are the special features of some models, such as what allows to reduce the dimensions of the PowerPoint presentation, useful for example for electronic transfer, or the ability to transfer a PDF folder to a graphic design model and preserve the original appearance of the page.
From this point of view, we can still create "PDF hybrid" documents that resemble typical Adobe graphics and have the characteristics of a spreadsheet or word processing program.
Collaboration is an element that has received many improvements within application programs: in Excel it is possible to work together between different users and avoid conflicts on changes, in a text program each collaborator is assigned one color for comments to make identification clearer in the revision phase.
Some companies are also working on porting some of Open Office's features to the Web (on the cloud), and should present a definitive result in the coming weeks.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html, it has been added to the English version, which can be found on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, as usual, the package is also available for the Linux operating system.
Also, the installation CD can be sent to your home or workplace on request.
And if the topic of free care can be a draw for expansion in households, the Open Office package is betting a lot on the business area, and it can already count on various projects implemented in public administration and schools.
And there are also offers of training, consultation and assistance services ideal for small and medium-sized companies, which could open up business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main models: Writer, for video typing replacing Word; Calc is a spreadsheet program that is moving towards replacing Excel; Impress for Powerpoint-like presentations; Dbase, as in the case of the more famous Access, is a program that allows you to work on databases; Draw, after all, is a graphical model.
The goal for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today we are at almost 3 million and 600 thousand, with the release of the new version it is possible that this expected number may even be exceeded.
